## Dependency Methodology

Dependencies were included only when supported by:

- Business dependency map;
- Business product catalog matrix;
- global opportunity registry;
- portfolio gated advancement review;
- nucleus maturity/status/blocker evidence.

Plausible but undocumented dependencies were listed under `Unverified / Needs Documentation` and were not promoted into official dependency entries.

## Nucleus-Level Dependency Summary

Business is the central dependency-mapping and readiness layer, but not an execution authority. It maps dependencies to Core, Governance, Defi, Dex, Marketplace, Trading, Academy, Mining, ACS, AxodusAPP, Documentation, Lottery and BBA-Agency.

Execution-sensitive ownership remains with the owning nuclei:

- Governance owns proposal/vote/executor authority.
- Defi/Treasury owns treasury, custody and settlement.
- Dex owns swaps/routing/liquidity execution.
- Trading owns exchange execution and credentials.
- Marketplace owns settlement, payment, minting and value transfer.
- Mining owns provider custody/accounting/payouts.
- ACS owns provisioning, agents, memory and workflow execution.
- Lottery owns randomness, prizes and payouts.

## Opportunity-Level Dependency Summary

Each of the 25 official opportunity registry entries now has a primary dependency record. High-sensitivity opportunities are explicitly blocking execution or production until the relevant review path is complete.

